coreInfo.label: Form Portal Deployment
coreInfo.assumptions:
1. Only Qualifacts team will have access to the Form Portal
  2. All required functionality needed for the Form Portal is exposed via APIs and is consumed from the browser (PWA)
  3. All required functionality needed by CareLogic is exposed via APIs and can be consumed either via Browser or from the Web Application Server (Carelogic Legacy)
coreInfo.justification:
• No violation of firewalls or communication between environments needed
  • It is cost effective
  • Provides Out of the Box capabilities to create Stages (Workflows to promote forms between environments)
coreInfo.motivation: Finding the right balance between licensing, separation of environments and business requirements when referring to the Form.io Portal
coreInfo.problemStatement: Qualifacts has a policy that states that all environments must be separated from each other, hence, no network communication exists between environments. Form.io states that one portal is enough to manage all environments even if they are separated by a firewall.
coreInfo.implications: We still need to check how it works with our Oauth Server instances. We have one instance per environment but they connect to the same user directory.

coreInfo.label: One Portal Per Environment
coreInfo.description:
• Qualifacts could acquire licenses to install independent Form Portals in each environment.
  • Each environment would be fully functional on its own, having all components that build up Form.io (DB, API Server, PDF Server and Portal Server)
  • Forms promotion should be done by an external component that emulates the portal functionality (export / import)

coreInfo.label: One Portal Server for all Environments
coreInfo.bestApplied:
• Form creation will be done in development environment
  • Only internal teams needs access to these servers
coreInfo.description:
• Acquire licenses for a single Portal Instance that manages all environments
  • The portal is a PWA that calls API services from the web browser
  • No inter environment communication is required

coreInfo.label: Consume Back End Services
coreInfo.assumptions:
• We can reuse the existing User Session (token) to consume the APIs from the API Gateway
  • Form.io gives back to the client application all the information needed to call backend services to populate fields (dropdowns, checkboxes, radio buttons, etc)
coreInfo.problemStatement:
• Forms created with Form.io will need to access backend services (from carelogic-domains) to populate data, for instance, a dropdown needs values for marital status: SINGLE, MARRIED, DIVORCED, etc.
  • Form.io is designed so that these services are consumed from the web browser
  • Services are exposed through an API Gateway and might be protected

coreInfo.label: Consume Services directly from the API Gateway
coreInfo.description:
Use a direct communication between browser and API Gateway to fill dropdown values, checkboxes or to consume any other data needed by Form.io forms.

  • No extra development is required
  • Fewer hops so better load time perception is expected for the end user
  • Will need to test and check for CORS issues

coreInfo.label: Use CareLogic web as Proxy
coreInfo.description:
All calls from the web browser to fill data would be directed to CareLogic Web as a proxy to the API Gateway

  • CareLogic already consumes backend services from the gateway
  • Will be needed in case we cannot reuse the TOKEN already in place to consume services from the API Gateway directly from the browser.
  • Will need to implement a "generic proxy" to consume various backend services

coreInfo.label: OAuth Server for Form IO Portal
coreInfo.assumptions:
• All instances of the Oauth2 Server are linked to the same User Repository.
  • FormIO can only be linked to one Oauth Server
coreInfo.justification: Still need to test how it works.
coreInfo.problemStatement: Form.IO is a system composed of a Form Portal (and Form Manager), API Server, PDF Server and Databases. While the last 3 are designed to have an instance per environment (DEV, QA, PROD, etc), the Form Portal is designed to have a unique instance capable of interact and manage the other 3 components. Users authenticate with an external Identity Provider, in our case, a custom implementation of Oauth2 Server based on Spring Security. There is an instance of the Oauth Server per environment so we need to decide which instance to use, considering that we Form Portal will be instanced in development environment.
coreInfo.implications:
This decisions will have implication in future projects:
Agencies will be able to edit their own forms through the Production CareLogic application that will embed the Form Portal or Form Manager
There is a project in place to replace current Oauth Servers with a third pary service (Ping Identity / Ping One).
Agencies may want to use their own directory servers masked by Ping One.

coreInfo.label: Use Production Oauth Server
coreInfo.description:
• Better availability of the Oauth Server
  • Better support

coreInfo.label: Use non Production Srever
coreInfo.description:
• Considering that the Form Portal will be enabled in Development environment, we might need to use the Dev Oauth Server not to violate any firewall restrictions
  • Only QSI users will interact with the Form Portal so Dev might be enough
  • Oauth Server might not be available as part of its own development backlog / lifecyce

coreInfo.label: 1) Browse CareLogic
coreInfo.description: This represents the regular use of CareLogic by a Clinician, loading a page that contains a form.

coreInfo.label: 2) Load CareLogic
coreInfo.description: CareLogic Web is requested for a specific web page that contains a form.

coreInfo.label: 4) Get Form
coreInfo.description: CareLogic asks Form.io for a specific form.

coreInfo.label: 5) Assemble Blank Form
coreInfo.description: Form.io assembles the form based on its form definition.

coreInfo.label: 6) Populate Field 1 (Session Token + Params)
coreInfo.description: Once the page along with the form.io form is loaded, some fields need to populate data like Marital Status, the web browser makes a call directly to the API Gateway.

coreInfo.label: 3) Load CareLogic Data
coreInfo.description: CareLogic calls for some back end services to fill data in the web page.

coreInfo.description: It is the main system being integrated with FormIO.

coreInfo.description: System that provides the forms to fill Service Document data

coreInfo.label: API Gateway
coreInfo.description: For simplicity of the diagram, this component represents the API gateway / backend services needed to populate some of the fields placed in the forms such as marital status or gender.

coreInfo.label: API Gateway
coreInfo.description: System that protects back end service, mainly provided by CareLogic Domains

coreInfo.label: CareLogic Domains
coreInfo.description: System that exposes back end services that will be used to fill form data. Architecturally, it may not change but we have to identify if we require new APIs.

coreInfo.label: QSI - Form Developer
coreInfo.description: It is responsible to create complex forms that require deeper development skills. Has to make sure that only "ready" forms are moved to DEV-LIVE project so they can be promoted to other environments.

coreInfo.label: QSI - ADMIN
coreInfo.description: It is the main responsible to build forms in Form.io. It is shown in this diagram for its implications in creating forms in dev environments  and tentatively promoting to next environments.

coreInfo.label: QSI - Impl Analyst
coreInfo.description: It is the main responsible to build forms in Form.io. It is shown in this diagram for its implications in creating forms in Cert environments and makes sure that "ready" forms are moved to Cert-Live so that they can be eventually be promoted to Prod Environment.

coreInfo.label: QSI - Dev Admin
coreInfo.description: It is the main responsible to build forms in Form.io. It is shown in this diagram for its implications in creating forms in dev environments  and tentatively promoting to next environments.
